---
---
<section class="premise" id="about" aria-labelledby="premise-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="premise-inner">

      <div class="premise-text">
        <h2 class="premise-heading" id="premise-heading">
          What the film is
        </h2>
        <p class="premise-body">
          A documentary short about Americans from many walks of life &ndash; the weekend
          gardener, the lifelong naturalist, the family on the grand estate &ndash; who turned
          the unused parts of their yards into native meadows, and got the fireflies, the
          butterflies, and the community back.
        </p>

        <dl class="film-meta">
          <div class="film-meta-row">
            <dt>Status</dt>
            <dd>In Production &ndash; 2026</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="film-meta-row">
            <dt>Runtime</dt>
            <dd>12&ndash;15 minutes</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="film-meta-row">
            <dt>Director</dt>
            <dd>Wylie Overstreet</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="film-meta-row">
            <dt>Producer</dt>
            <dd>Nick Lyon</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="film-meta-row">
            <dt>Producer</dt>
            <dd>Mel Finn</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="film-meta-row">
            <dt>Created by</dt>
            <dd>William Sweet</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="film-meta-row">
            <dt>Production</dt>
            <dd>Painted Wolf Pictures &times; BirdStory</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </div>

      <div class="premise-image">
        <figure class="premise-figure">
          <img
            class="img-premise"
            src="/images/meadow-project-litchfield.webp"
            alt="Meadow Project, Litchfield County, Connecticut — native planting in progress"
            width="960"
            height="623"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption class="img-credit">Photo: Larry Weaner Landscape Associates (LWLA)</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .premise {
    padding: var(--space-24) 0;
  }

  .premise-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 3fr 2fr;
    gap: var(--space-16);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .premise-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .premise-body {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 65ch;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .premise-body:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .premise-figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .img-premise {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    display: block;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .img-credit {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-wildflower);
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
    text-align: right;
  }

  .film-meta {
    margin-top: var(--space-10);
    padding-top: var(--space-8);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-amber);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }

  .film-meta-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 9ch 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    align-items: baseline;
  }

  .film-meta dt {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-earth);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .film-meta dd {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    opacity: 0.75;
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .premise-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-8);
    }

    .premise-image {
      order: -1;
    }
  }
</style>
